The paper discusses classification using deep neural networks and proposes a generative approach to address the problem of incorrect labels being provided with high confidence to out of distribution examples. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper also discusses safety against adversarial examples, which falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the proposed method involves the use of generative models such as GANs and VAEs, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
